<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gonzalez Closes 33d PSOE Congress </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003182694 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1800 GMT 
20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003182694 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The 33d congress of the Spanish Socialist Workers 
Party [PSOE] has ended. Party Secretary General Felipe 
Gonzalez closed the congress. Antonio Criado reports from 
Madrid's Palace of Congresses. 
  [Criado] This congress will go down in history because it 
marks the difference between one period and another. This is 
what Secretary General Felipe Gonzalez said in his closing 
address to the 33d congress. According to Felipe Gonzalez this 
has been the best congress in the past 20 years. In short, he 
was extremely satisfied both with the renewal and the 
integration that the party has undergone. According to Felipe 
Gonzalez, wounds have to be healed with generosity -- a 
generosity that has to be extended to integration of all wings 
in the party during the provincial congresses. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

