<H3> <TI>   Delors Discusses Fishing Issue With Balladur </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803130194 Paris AFP in English 1245 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1803130194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 18 (AFP) -- French Prime Minister 
Edouard Balladur met on Friday morning [18 March] with European 
Commission president Jacques Delors to discuss "all European 
questions", Delors said after the talk. 
  He said that during their meeting lasting almost 45 minutes, 
the two men had discussed "fishing, efforts the community is 
going to make to help in restructuring and modernizing the 
French fishing fleet, and the enlargement of the European Union 
and institutional problems relating to that issue". 
  He added that they had discussed the situation of Air France 
airline, the national carrier. 
  Both men are potential French presidential candidates in 
next 
year's elections. 

</TEXT>

