<H3> <TI>   Balladur `Encouraged' by Results </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2003225794 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 2130 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2003225794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement on first round of cantonal elections by Prime </F>
Minister Edouard Balladur -- recorded] 
  [Text] The first round confirms the trust of the French in 
the majority which they elected last year. It can even be said 
that it is stronger than it was last year. This also indicates 
that, despite the current difficulties, the French have the 
feeling that the majority and the government are doing 
everything they can to get the country on its feet again. It is 
difficult, more difficult than you can imagine, but we are very 
encouraged by this result. You all said that this would be a 
test -- I did not, you did -- well the test is here and I have 
the feeling that [the results have been] rather favorable for us. 

</TEXT>

