<F P=101> Sweden </F>
<H3> <TI>   National Referendum on EU Planned for 13 Nov </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1803132794 Stockholm Radio Sweden in Swedish 1130 GMT 18 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1803132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Radio Sweden </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Swedish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] It is finally clear, Sunday,13 November will be 
the day of the national referendum on the European Union [EU], 
the party leaders agreed today. This means that Prime Minister 
Carl Bildt, who wanted to have the national referendum in June, 
has given in to the Social Democrats who wanted to have the 
national referendum in November. The most important thing is 
that in this way Sweden can become a member on 1 January next 
year, Carl Bildt says. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

