<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Receives Greek Defense Minister </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1803172094 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1803172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis described the decisions 
made by the Greek and Cypriot Defense Ministries as significant 
steps toward strengthening Cyprus' defense. In a statement this 
afternoon, after meeting Greek and Cypriot Defense Ministers 
Yerasimos Arsenis and Konstandinos Iliadhis, who briefed him on 
the decisions made, Kliridhis described the work that has been 
made as significant. He added that he is happy because Cyprus' 
defense is safeguarded by the decisions made. He also expressed 
his respect for the Greek prime minister and defense minister 
for implementing the joint defense doctrine. 
  Arsenis said he was satisfied because the agreement is being 
realized. He added that measures have been taken to strengthen 
Greek-Cypriot defense cooperation in all sectors. He added that 
the two ministers agreed to meet regularly to follow 
developments in the implementation of the decisions. The 
National Defense General Staff and the National Guard General 
Staff will establish a joint committee to examine and suggest 
measures about the plans according to the situation at that 
time. He said that many of the measures that have been decided 
during the talks cannot be announced. 
  Iliadhis said the National Guard will be reinforced with new 
members and new arms systems. He added that National Guard 
members will participate in joint military maneuvers. 

</TEXT>

