<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Committee With Kurdistan Chairman Murdered </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2003220294 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 2138 
GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2003220294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CyBC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unscheduled news flash] </F>
  [Text] It has just been announced that Theofilos 
Yeoryiadhis, 37, a turkologist and chairman of the Committee of 
Solidarity With Kurdistan, was murdered in Nicosia tonight. 
Yeoryiadhis was shot in the parking lot of a three-story 
building on Thoukidhidhou Street in Aglanja where he lived with 
his family. According to a female witness living at a nearby 
house, two people were seen escaping on a motorcycle immediately 
after the shooting. The area has been blocked off by police and 
the police chief and director of the criminal investigation 
department are there. 
  Yeoryiadhis is the father of three children aged 13, eight, 
and 10 months. 

</TEXT>

