<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish `Agents' Accused </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2103073794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 0530 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2103073794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Government spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis condemned 
the murder of Theofilos Yeoryiadhis, chairman of the Committee 
of Solidarity with Kurdistan, adding that he probably fell 
victim to Turkish Security Service agents. In a statement to 
the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation, Kasoulidhis said: We 
should not consider Yeoryiadhis' murder to have anything in 
particular to do with Cyprus. Such murders, Kasoulidhis added, 
have been taking place lately in various European countries and 
elsewhere. But, he said, if the aim was to affect the talks on 
the Cyprus issue, [Turkish Cypriot leader Rauf] Denktas will not 
avoid assuming his responsibilities on the talks on the 
confidence-building measures. 
  EDEK [United Democratic Union of Cyprus] Chairman Vasos 
Lissaridhis said the murder was political, a challenge to 
everyone. He said this is the Turkish answer we get: the murder 
of a genuine man of the people in our country. Lissaridhis 
added that Yeoryiadhis was a man with ideals and principles and 
his actions were always within political boundaries. 
  DISI [Democratic Rally] General Secretary Dhimitrios 
Sillouris said Turks perpetrated Yeoryiadhis' murder. He said 
he is certain this is not the last such act we will see, adding 
that it must be organized, something directly connected with the 
advance of the confidence-building measures. Sillouris said 
Turkish agents circulate unhampered in the free areas of the 
Republic of Cyprus and added that we should all assume our 
responsibilities and protect ourselves through the state 
structure and through cooperation between people and the 
responsible authorities. 
  Yeoryiadhis' murder was also condemned by AKEL's 
[Restorative 
Party of the Working People] press spokesman Nikolaos 
Katsouridhis and DIKO [Democratic Party] Deputy Nikolaos 
Mousiouttas. 
  The National Liberation Front of Kurdistan has strongly 
condemned Yeoryiadhis' murder, which, it says in a statement, 
was planned by the Turkish National Security Council and 
executed by the Turkish Secret Service. The statement also 
notes that the National Liberation Front of Kurdistan will reply 
accordingly to the Attila state, which destroys the people of 
Kurdistan with Ottoman and Mongolian methods. 

</TEXT>

