<H3> <TI>   Pangalos Calls EU Expansion `Wrong, Premature' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1803052694 Athens ET-1 Television Network in Greek 2130 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1803052694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ET-1 Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Greek Alternate Foreign Minister Theodhoros 
Pangalos said that the expansion of the European Union [EU] was 
a mistake, and warned that it could threaten the EU's ability to 
make decisions on its future. Pangalos also warned that the 
possible election of an extreme right coalition in Italy, which 
would be neofascistic, could cause a big political problem for 
Europe. Despite the fact that Pangalos chaired the successful 
negotiations for the accession of four new members to the 
European Union, he stressed: Now that this is over, now that I 
have done my duty, I honestly want to say that this decision was 
a mistake. 
  [Begin recording] [Pangalos] I want to say that the 
decision on the expansion of the European Union was wrong and 
premature. The European Union should not have proceeded to 
assume new responsibilities before the EU's structure was 
deepened, before we made substantial institutional and economic 
changes, and before we finished implementing the Maastricht 
Treaty. [passage omitted] [end recording] 

</TEXT>

