<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poland's Kolodziejczyk Relays Walesa Message </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1803093094 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 2200 
GMT 17 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1803093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Polish National Defense Minister Piotr 
Kolodziejczyk, who is currently on an official visit in Turkey, 
conducted contacts in Ankara today. 
  President Suleyman Demirel received the Polish minister at 
the Cankaya Mansion. In a statement during the meeting, Demirel 
said that the friendly relations between the two countries date 
back 579 years and the first friendship agreement was signed on 
23 July 1923. Pointing out that businessmen from the two 
countries can cooperate in Turkey as well as in third countries, 
Demirel explained that Poland is successfully managing the 
process of democratic transformation and transition to a free 
market economy within the framework of the reforms it is 
implementing. Turkey is according the necessary support to 
Poland on the international and bilateral levels, Demirel 
remarked, adding that the Partnership for Peace project proposed 
by NATO constitutes an important move. 
  In his statement, Kolodziejczyk conveyed to Demirel a 
friendship message from Polish President Walesa and expressed 
gratitude for Turkey's support and contribution to the 
Partnership for Peace project with regard to membership in NATO. 
The Polish defense minister noted that his country wishes to 
benefit from Turkey's recent achievements, especially from its 
experience in the defense industry field. 

</TEXT>

