<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Council Meets; Ciller on Speculation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1803124394 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1803124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Excerpts] The Supreme Military Council met in an 
extraordinary session under the chairmanship of Prime Minister 
Tansu Ciller in Ankara today. 
  In an opening statement, Ciller expressed the belief that 
decisions that will contribute to the development of the Armed 
Forces will be adopted at the meeting. She remarked that the 
Turkish Armed Forces fulfill their task with regard to internal 
security in a spirit of self-sacrifice and discharge the duties 
they assume abroad with a view to contributing to world peace. 
[passage omitted] 
  [Begin Ciller recording] The Armed Forces constitute the 
most important guarantee of the country's security and our 
independence. Certain circles that are well aware of this fact 
are engaged in speculations concerning the Turkish Armed Forces 
-- either knowingly, because they are not friends of this 
country, or unknowingly. This saddens us all. Nevertheless, we 
know very well and we believe that our lofty nation is assessing 
the events in the most correct way on the basis of its boundless 
common sense and is aware of the motives behind them. [end 
recording] [passage omitted] 
  In a statement about the Supreme Military Council meeting, 
Staff Colonel Dogu Silahcioglu, spokesman of the General Staff, 
declared that the political and military situation in light of 
developments in surrounding countries was assessed during the 
meeting. According to the statement, proposals for changes in 
the legal procedures concerning the Turkish Armed Forces were 
also discussed at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

