<H3> <TI>   Iranian Authorities Hand Over 16 `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2003164694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 20 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2003164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, March 20 (A.A) -- Interior Minister Nahit 
Mentese said today that Iranian authorities handed 16 
terrorists, including two dead, to Turkey. 
  In a written statement, Mentese said that the government had 
made important gains against terrorists and that 160 separatist 
terrorists, including 78 dead, were caught by security forces in 
the last week. 
  Three missile launchers, 20 missile launcher shells, 28 
long-range guns, 5 revolvers, 22 hand grenades, and ammunition 
were seized in the recent searches. 

