<H3> <TI>   Debt Rescheduling Agreement Signed With Iran </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103150794 Vienna DER STANDARD in German 21 Mar 94 p 13 </F>
<F P=103> AU2103150794 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DER STANDARD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report signed "wip": "Austrian Rescheduling Agreement With </F>
Iran Signed"] 
  [Excerpt] Vienna -- Iran has now successfully concluded 
its negotiations with Austria on rescheduling credits with 
Austrian state guarantees. The new agreement will settle the 
repayment of short-term loans of 5.6 billion schillings, 
including the interest accumulated. 
  Austria has granted Iran a suspension of payments for 
outstanding capital until 1 July 1996. At that point, Iran will 
pay back its debts in 16 quarterly installments. As far as the 
accumulated debt is concerned, repayment is to be in 16 monthly 
installments to start on 30 June 1994. On the basis of the 
agreement on Iran's debts, Austrian exporters can now hope for 
new Control Bank guarantees. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

