<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   More Blue Helmets, Radar Unit to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2103180594 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 1400 GMT 21 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2103180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In answer to the UN's request for more troops on 
humanitarian missions in Bosnia, a total of 145 Spanish blue 
helmets are traveling to the area between Monday [21 March] and 
Tuesday to reinforce the 1,200 members of the Madrid Group. In 
April the Canaries Group will replace the Madrid one, which has 
been stationed in Bosnia since autumn. 
  A radar detector unit left Madrid on Monday. It comprises 25 
men, 15 vehicles, and an antimortar radar. Its mission is to 
monitor the cease-fire in the city of Mostar. 
  On Tuesday 120 men will leave Seville. Once deployed in the 
conflict area, they will reinforce the monitoring operations and 
will be involved in the rebuilding of Mostar. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

