<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Envoy Clark Arrives for Talks on CBM's </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1903203194 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 1830 
GMT 19 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1903203194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CyBC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Joe Clark, the UN secretary general's special 
representative in Cyprus, arrived to Cyprus tonight. In a 
statement at Larnaca Airport, Clark said that during his 
presence in Cyprus he looks forward to constructive talks. He 
added that it is important that everyone knows that time is 
passing and that with this set of events we want to conclude an 
agreement on the confidence-building measures [CBM's] as soon as 
possible. And if this is not possible, we must know it as soon 
as possible. 
  Clark said that as a practical measure we want a clear 
indication by the end of the week when the UN secretary general 
will submit his report to the Security Council. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

