<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Turkish Foreign Ministry Officials Arrive for Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2103171294 Nicosia Bayrak Radio in Turkish 1530 GMT 21 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2103171294 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Bayrak Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tugay Ulucevik, Turkish Foreign Ministry deputy 
under secretary, has declared that if the content of the 
confidence-building measures package is eroded during the course 
of the proximity talks, then naturally the Turkish Cypriot side 
will have to make a reassessment of the situation. Ulucevik 
arrived in the island today to be briefed by Turkish Cypriot 
officials with regard to the latest phase of the talks 
concerning the confidence-building measures package. 
  In a statement to a TAK [Turkish Cypriot News Agency] 
correspondent at Ercan [Tymbou] State Airport, Ulucevik said 
that, on the basis of the conviction that the package will 
facilitate a comprehensive solution, Turkey and the Turkish 
Republic of Northern Cyprus will not in principle change their 
attitude unless the package is amended. 
  Ulucevik is accompanied by Ertugrul Apakan, Turkish Foreign 
Ministry's deputy director for Greek and Cypriot affairs. 
Ulucevik and Apakan will remain in north Cyprus for two days. 

</TEXT>

