<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Perpetrator Reportedly `Hit Man' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2203124194 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2203124194 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] The perpetrator of Theofilos Yeoryiadhis' 
horrible murder was a professional hit man acting according to a 
careful plan for which he needed much accurate information. 
This is the result of the Criminal Investigation Department's 
investigations so far and it reinforces the belief that Turkey's 
secret agencies planned the murder some time ago. 
  The culprit used a semi-automatic gun or a small automatic 
gun using special technology. The Criminal Investigation 
Department is convinced that if the culprit has not escaped to 
the occupied areas, he could be located and arrested. But the 
hit man could have crossed the buffer zone five minutes after 
the murder. According to the same reports, the culprits could 
have escaped to the occupied areas even with a car. This 
afternoon, the police are expected to release the sketches of 
two people who were seen moving in a suspicious manner while 
riding in a yellow Mercedes a few hours before the murder. The 
description of one of the men matches eyewitness descriptions of 
the man they saw approach and shoot Theofilos from a Vespa 
motorcycle. [passage omitted] 
  In a statement to the Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation, 
Former 
National Guard Chief Dhimitrios Matafias confirmed that several 
Turkish press reports list him as a target of Turkey's secret 
services. Matafias reportedly met the Kurdish movement's 
leadership eight years ago and since then has supported the 
Kurds both financially and in other ways. 
  Commenting on information that he will be the next Turkish 
target, Matafias said he believes the Turks use these methods to 
intimidate or make an impression and thus strangle every voice 
in support of the Kurds. He added that he must take some 
additional protection measures. 

</TEXT>

