<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Committee Condemns Assassination </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2103190594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1700 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2103190594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Cyprus Committee of Solidarity With Kurdistan 
revealed that in the past Theofilos Yeoryiadhis received many 
telephone calls from people speaking Turkish who threatened to 
kill him. It was also revealed that, according to information 
at the committee's disposal, one of the next possible targets of 
Turkish secret agents is Lieutenant General Dhimitrios Matafias, 
former National Guard Commander, who is considered to play a 
leading role in Greek activities in support of the Kurds. The 
committee has briefed the Greek police about this information. 
  These revelations were made by members of the Committee of 
Solidarity With Kurdistan at a news conference this afternoon on 
the abominable assassination of Theofilos Yeoryiadhis. The news 
conference was given in the House of Representatives building in 
the presence of representatives from all the parliamentary 
parties, which condemned the assassination and praised the 
personality of the fighter for human rights, Theofilos 
Yeoryiadhis. 
  On behalf of the House of Representatives, Vasos 
Lissaridhis, 
EDEK [United Democratic Union of Cyprus] chairman, said that a 
House delegation will visit New York to condemn the ongoing 
oppression of the Kurdish people and the assassination of 
Theofilos Yeoryiadhis to the UN secretary general. Mr. 
Lissaridhis also said that the infiltration of Turkish agents 
into the free areas will be raised for debate by the House 
plenary session. 
  Speaking on behalf of the Committee of Solidarity With 
Kurdistan, Lazaros Mavros said that the action of the Turkish 
secret agencies has also extended into the free areas of Cyprus. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

