<H3> <TI>   Constitutional Court Restores Immunity of DEP Deputy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2103170494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1505 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA2103170494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, Mar 21 (AA) -- The Constitutional Court on 
Monday [21 March] reversed parliament's decision to remove 
Democracy Party (DEP) Deputy Selim Sadak's parliamentary 
immunity. 
  The court refused to reverse parliament's decision 
concerning 
the immunity of the other five DEP deputies and an independent 
deputy. 
  Parliament on March 2, removed the immunity of six DEP 
members, a former party member, an anti-Kemalist and an 
independent. 
  The DEP deputies, who were arrested last week by the court, 
are charged with crimes against the state. 

</TEXT>

