<H3> <TI>   Last German UN Soldiers Leave Somalia 18 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803132494 Hamburg DPA in German 1258 GMT 18 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- The last German Blue Helmet soldier 
left Somalia on Friday [18 March] at 1400 local time -- 1200 
Central European Time. This was stated by the Defense Ministry 
in Bonn. The last 180 soldiers of the German units were flown 
to the Cologne and Karlsruhe frigates by helicopter. The naval 
unit has left for Djibouti, where it is expected to arrive on 
Tuesday. From there, the soldiers will fly back home on 
Wednesday, and will be welcome by Defense Minister Volker Ruehe, 
of the Christian Democratic Union, at the military section of 
Cologne/Bonn Airport. 

</TEXT>

