<H3> <TI>   Lufthansa To Retrain PRC Combat Pilots </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2103162494 Hamburg DPA in German 1513 GMT 21 Mar 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2103162494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bremen (DPA) -- Lufthansa in Bremen will retrain 76 
Chinese combat pilots as pilots for passenger planes. The young 
pilots are to arrive at the Lufthansa passenger plane pilot 
school in Phoenix, Arizona, by the end of this month. The 
tender was issued by Air China, the largest of the seven Chinese 
airlines. 
  Lufthansa hopes that it will subsequently be able to take 
over the training program for the Boeing 737, which would be 
held in Bremen. Since aviation is increasing in China, 
thousands of pilots have to be trained, a Lufthansa spokesman 
said. At the end of the 1980's, the passenger plane pilot 
school took over consulting tasks at the pilot school in central 
China. 

</TEXT>

