<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> France </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Gauges Popularity of Politicians, Parties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1703112694 Paris PARIS MATCH in French 17 Mar 94 pp 
78-79--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1703112694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris PARIS MATCH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> ["PARIS MATCH"-B.V.A. Opinion Poll: "Balladur Down Two </F>
Points: End of His Period of Grace, for 58 Percent of the 
French, He Lulls the People. Juppe Enjoys Highest Confidence 
Rating: Up Nine Points"] 
  [Text] The latest PARIS MATCH-B.V.A. opinion poll discloses 
that the period of grace which the prime minister was enjoying, 
is over. Edouard Balladur's popularity dropped by 2 percent, 
although he is still supported by 53 percent of the people. Our 
survey reveals that 58 percent of the French think that he has a 
tendency to lull the French to sleep; 51 percent think he does 
not speak the truth. An absolute majority of those interviewed 
think that the prime minister has the style of a head of state, 
but there is also a negative side to this: 51 percent state 
that he thinks too much about the presidential election. 
Francois Mitterrand sees his popularity ratings rise by 3 
percent, tilting the balance between positive and negative 
opinions into the positive region again. The big winner in this 
confidence poll is [Foreign Minister] Alain Juppe, whose rating 
soars by 9 percent. 


