|(19 percent of persons registered did not express their voting intention)    | 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


  This survey was conducted on a sample representative of the 
French population aged 18 years and over. The question 
referring to legislative election voting intentions was asked to 
2,948 persons between 15 and 18 February and between 1 and 4 
March 1994; the other questions were out to 973 persons between 
1 and 4 March. Voting intentions are calculated on the basis of 
the number of persons registered for the elections. Sampling 
was done according to the quota method: sex; age; occupation of 
family head; and region and area (city, rural...). Results 
should be interpreted taking into account the usual error 
margins related to any poll and the size of the sample. There 
error margins are: approximately one to two points for voting 
intentions; approximately two to three points for the overall 
results; approximately four to five points for the results 
referring to the large political families. 

</TEXT>

