<H3> <TI>   France Urges UN To Issue `Very Firm Warning' to DPRK </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203153994 Paris AFP in English 1519 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2203153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Paris, March 22 (AFP) -- France would like the UN 
Security Council to impose sanctions against North Korea unless 
the latter agrees to full inspections of its nuclear facilities, 
Foreign Ministry spokesman Richard Duque said Tuesday [22 March]. 
  He said the Security Council should issue a "very firm 
warning" to convince Pyongyang to allow inspectors from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA) to carry out the 
necessary inspections. 
  The IAEA Board of Governors decided Monday to refer the 
North 
Korean nuclear issue to the UN Security Council. 
  Speculation has increased that the Council might decide on 
punitive action against North Korea, suspected of developing 
nuclear weapons. 

</TEXT>

