<H3> <TI>   EU Urged To Adopt Uniform Position on NPT </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2103115194 Brussels EUROPE in English 17 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2103115194 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels EUROPE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "EP Energy Committee Calls For </F>
Clauses on Nuclear Non-Proliferation To Be Included in 
Cooperation Agreements"; as released by Brussels TEXTLINE 
database] 
  [Text] Brussels, 17 Mar 94 (AGENCE EUROPE) -- With the 
adoption of the report by Carlos Robles Piquer on the Nuclear 
Non-Proliferation Treaty which must be extended in 1995, the EP 
[European Parliament] Committee on Energy, Research and 
Technology has called on the European Union to define "as 
uniform a position as possible" on this issue in order to 
reinforce the guarantees against the risk of proliferation. 
According to MEPs, the European Union should tend, moreover, 
towards establishing an international and universal control 
system of the "complete cycle" of uranium, plutonium and 
possibly thorium, for civilian purposes. In addition, MEPs 
consider that, in the cooperation agreements with third 
countries, the Union should include clauses on the 
non-proliferation of nuclear weapons. Finally, MEPs took an 
explicit stand in favour of establishing a denuclearised zone in 
the Near East. 

</TEXT>

