<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- On 8 June, two days after the Allied 
ceremonies commemorating the 50th anniversary of the landing in 
Normandy, Chancellor Helmut Kohl and French President Francois 
Mitterrand will meet in Heidelberg with young people from the 
two countries. Speaking to reporters in Bonn on Wednesday [23 
March], Kohl also announced invitations to U.S. President Bill 
Clinton, Britain's Prime Minister John Major and Mitterrand to 
come to Berlin on 8 September for a Grand Tatoo to bid farewell 
to the Allied soldiers in the capital. 
  Russian President Boris Yeltsin, who will pay an official 
visit to Bonn from 11 to 13 May, will come on 31 August to bid 
farwell to the Russian soldiers, Kohl announced. The 
celebrations are planned in Berlin and Weimar with German and 
Russian military honor formations. 

