<H3> <TI>   Bundeswehr General Huber Offers To Resign </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803173594 Hamburg DPA in German 1415 GMT 18 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803173594 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Bonn -- The special representative for 
rationalization measures within the Bundeswehr, General Lorenz 
Huber, has asked for his dismissal. The Defense Ministry 
confirmed the step of the 57-year-old general today. As DPA 
learned, he cited lacking support for his proposed austerity 
measures by senior generals as the reason for his departure. 
The Defense Ministry announced that no decision has yet been 
made regarding Huber's request. The defense expert of the 
Christian Democratic Union, Paul Breuer, demanded the 
"unconditional examination of all of Huber's proposals and a 
clarification of the circumstances that prompted Huber to take 
this personal step." Juergen Koppelin from the Free Democratic 
Party of Germany spoke of a "serious warning" for Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe (Christian Democratic Union). [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

