<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Receives Syrian Minister, Discusses Ties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1803141494 Hamburg DPA in German 1256 GMT 18 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1803141494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- Federal Economics Minister Guenter 
Rexrodt, of the Free Democratic Party of Germany, hopes that the 
visit to Germany by Syrian Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' "will 
mark the beginning of intensifying bilateral economic 
relations." Rexrodt said that, apart from the developments of 
the Middle East peace process, his one-hour talk with Al-Shar' 
in Bonn on Friday [18 March] focussed on the possibilities for 
developing German-Syrian economic ties. 
  According to Rexrodt, Syrian exports to Germany totalled 
1.12 
billion German marks [DM] and were twice as high as German 
exports to Syria (DM546 million). The reason for the high 
Syrian trade balance surplus are Germany's oil imports from 
Syria. In the first 11 months of 1993, Germany's exports to 
Syria grew by 25 percent over the same period in the previous 
year, while imports from Syria only increased by 6 percent. 

</TEXT>

