<H3> <TI>   ENI's Privatization Operation Assessed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1803134394 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1846 GMT 17 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1803134394 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Privatization Earns National </F>
Hydrocarbons Corporation 2.7 Billion Lire"] 
  [Text] Rome, 17 Mar (ANSA) -- The privatization campaign 
carried out by the Italian state fuels group ENI [National 
Hydrocarbons Corporation] has already earned for the group some 
2.67 trillion lire, just over some 1.6 billion dollars. 
  The number of privatization operations carried out by ENI on 
Thursday [17 March] reached 48 with the sale of its interest in 
Liquipibigas to Novogas, for 245 billion lire, and Enichem 
synthesis interests to Great Lakes chemicals of the United 
States for 150 billion lire. 
  Overall, ENI so far has sold off is participation in 
companies, plants and real estate for an overall earning of 4 
trillion lire and involving some 11 thousand employees. 
  ENI has carried out its privatization operations based on 
competitive auctions, publicized both at home and abroad with 
appraisals given by the world's leading specialized institutions. 

</TEXT>

