<H3> <TI>   Ukrainian Nuclear Specialists Trained on Security </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR2103151794 Bern ATSA/SDAA in French 1302 GMT 21 Mar 
94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR2103151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bern ATSA/SDAA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed GB/PI/SH: "Ukrainian Nuclear Specialists </F>
Visit Goesgen"; as released by Bern ATSA/SDAA database] 
  [Text] Daeniken, 21 Mar (ATS) -- Five Ukrainian nuclear 
energy specialists took a training course at the Goesgen power 
station in Soleure Canton last week. The Swiss Association for 
Atomic Energy disclosed on Monday [21 March] that the training 
focused primarily on the security procedures at West European 
nuclear power stations. 
  The nuclear power plant operated by the five Ukrainian 
guests 
is located 150 km north of Odessa. It comprises three reactor 
units with a capacity of approximately 1,000 megawatts. As far 
as technology is concerned, it is similar to the Goesgen reactor. 

</TEXT>

