<H3> <TI>   * Fewer Asylum-Seekers in Nordic Countries Recorded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94EN0252D Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE in Danish 1 Mar 94 p 
10 </F>

<F P=103> 94EN0252D </F>
<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Danish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Fewer Applied for Asylum"] </F>
  [Text] The total number of asylum-seekers in the Nordic 
countries was cut in half from 1992 to last year. While a good 
107,000 people sought asylum in the Nordic lands in 1992, around 
67,000 requested asylum there in 1993, according to the latest 
figures from the United Nations. 

</TEXT>

