<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Companies Invest 11.5 Billion Schillings in Hungary </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2203133094 Vienna DIE PRESSE in German 22 Mar 94 p 18 </F>
<F P=103> AU2203133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna DIE PRESSE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Erich Hoorn: "Austria Has Invested 11.5 Billion </F>
Schillings in Hungary"] 
  [Excerpt] Austrian companies have concluded as many as 
2,700 joint ventures in Hungary. Josef Schwarz, Austrian trade 
delegate to Budapest, told DIE PRESSE in Vienna that investments 
there have reached 11.5 billion schillings. 
  Austrian companies have been particularly active as far as 
the privatization of Hungarian enterprises is concerned. The 
State Privatization Agency has so far sold 328 major public 
enterprises for 176.3 billion forints (the equivalent of about 
21 billion schillings) to foreigners, of which Austrian 
investors have bought 96 enterprises for 43.8 billion forints 
(5.3 billion schillings) -- that is to say about 25 percent. 
  The managing president of the Hungarian Joint Venture 
Association, Ivan Toldy-Osz, told DIE PRESSE in Sopron that some 
18,000 joint ventures and 100 percent subsidiaries by foreign 
companies have been registered in Hungary. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

