<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Feels Coalition To Remain After Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303121294 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1125 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2303121294 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN)--German Chancellor Helmut Kohl 
believes there is a "very good chance" that the governing 
coalition with the FDP [Free Democratic Party] can be continued 
after the Bundestag elections in October. Kohl also made it 
clear in Bonn today that he expects the Free Democrats to issue 
a coalition pledge in favor of the Union. The FDP has always 
known what is in its own best interests, Kohl said. He is 
confident they will continue to do so. In addition to this, they 
can hardly point out to voters the good work done by the 
coalition and at the same time announce its break-up. 

</TEXT>

