<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Brandenburg Ruling Coalition Collapses </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2203221194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 2121 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2203221194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Potsdam (DDP/ADN) -- The coalition in Brandenburg 
Land consisting of the Social Democratic Party [SPD], Free 
Democratic Party [FDP], and Alliance [the east German Greens] 
has finally collapsed six months before the land elections. 
Following the session of the coalition committee, the 
Brandenburg parliamentary group leaders announced the end of the 
trilateral alliance in Potsdam this evening. It appears that a 
minority government consisting of the SPD and FDP will govern 
the land in the future. The SPD has 35 seats in the 88-member 
Landtag; the FDP has six. 

</TEXT>

