<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   SPD, Liberals Form Coalition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2303094394 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0847 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2303094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Potsdam (DDP/ADN)--Brandenburg's Social Democrats 
and Liberals have agreed to a two-party coalition following the 
collapse of the trilateral alliance last night. SPD [Social 
Democratic Party] parliamentary group chairman Wolfgang Birthler 
told journalists in Potsdam today that the minority government 
would operate on the basis of the existing cooperation agreement 
reached in November 1990. Only the objective of devoting even 
greater effort toward the creation of jobs would be added to the 
existing coalition paper. 
  The Liberals intend to add further amendments following a 
private meeting this weekend. Both partners stressed their wish 
to continue their "successful policies as before" until the 
regular Landtag elections this autumn. There will be no 
fundamental break with previous government policy, Birthler said. 

</TEXT>

