<F P=101> Denmark </F>
<H3> <TI>   * Private Foreign Aid Agencies Increase Spending </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94EN0252C Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE in Danish 1 Mar 94 p 
7 </F>

<F P=103> 94EN0252C </F>
<F P=104>  Copenhagen BERLINGSKE TIDENDE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Danish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "More Aid"] </F>
  [Text] The four private aid organizations -- the State 
Church System's Emergency Aid, Ibis, the Danish Red Cross, and 
the Labor Unions' Developing Countries Secretariat -- will spend 
67.3 billion kroner more of DANIDA's [Danish International 
Development Authority] funds this year than the Folketing 
anticipated last year. 

</TEXT>

